Change History

Revision Date Notes
2.0.0 2019-07-17 Added RouterLog2 service to indicate the following actions now requires authentication:
  • GetLogSettings
  • GetIncomingLogEntries
  • GetOutgoingLogEntries
  • GetSecurityLogEntries
  • GetDHCPLogEntries
1.0.1 2017-03-08 Added "Request" value to DHCPMessageType enum.

Services

RouterLog

http://linksys.com/jnap/routerlog/RouterLog
This service provides access to a router's log settings.

Service Actions

  • DeleteLogEntries
  • GetDHCPLogEntries
  • GetIncomingLogEntries
  • GetLogSettings
  • GetOutgoingLogEntries
  • GetSecurityLogEntries
  • SetLogSettings

Actions

DeleteLogEntries

http://linksys.com/jnap/routerlog/DeleteLogEntries
This action deletes all log entries on the router.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/routerlog/DeleteLogEntriesResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorDisallowedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/routerlog/DeleteLogEntries"

{
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK"
}

GetDHCPLogEntries

http://linksys.com/jnap/routerlog/GetDHCPLogEntries
This action gets the oldest DHCP client log entries for the router.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
firstEntryIndex int no Index of first entry to return. Indices begin with 1.
entryCount int no Maximum number of entries to return.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
entries DHCPClientEntry[] no Log entries for DHCP client.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/routerlog/GetDHCPLogEntriesResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorInvalidEntryCount The specified entry count was less than 1.
ErrorInvalidFirstEntryIndex The specified first entry index was less than 1.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/routerlog/GetDHCPLogEntries"

{
  "firstEntryIndex": 1,
  "entryCount": 64
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "entries": [
      {
        "timestamp": "2016-07-23T14:30:59Z",
        "messageType": "Discover",
        "macAddress": "00:22:5F:A1:73:C1",
        "ipAddress": "192.168.1.101"
      }
    ]
  }
}
